housing_pipeline.description:
The proposed project will replace an existing surface parking lot with a 400-foot-tall, mixed-use, residential building with 3,767 sq. ft. of retail space facing 3rd and Harrison Streets, 522 dwelling units, and accessory below-grade parking. The project will utilize a 50% State Density Bonus including the following waivers and incentives (with modifications since the time of initial project approval dated June 29, 2023): 

Waivers:
(1) Sections 132.4 and 132.4(d)(2)(B) (required setbacks); 
(2) Sections 250(b) and 841.01 (height limit); 
(3) Sections 270(h) and 841.02 (bulk limit); 
(4) Section 249.78(d)(9) (wind comfort); 
(5) Sections 135 and 841.11 (open space, residential, changed from incentive); and 
(6) Section 207.6 (required dwelling unit mix in the Eastern Neighborhoods Mixed-Use District - added).

Incentives and Concessions:
(1) Section 132.4(d)(1)(A) (street wall); and
(2) Section 415 (collapse inclusionary affordable housing tiers; pay in-lieu of fee - added).

Project modifications to 395 3rd Street since the initial project approvals (2021-003762ENX) at the Planning Commission on June 29, 2023 include:
(1) Increase in residential gross floor area from 455,812 sq. ft. to 482,485 sq. ft.;
(2) Increase in building height from 370 ft. to 391 ft. to the top of the penthouse roof;
(3) Increase in number of building stories from 35 stories to 37 stories;
(4) Increase in State Density Bonus from 42.5% to 50%; and
(5) Change in onsite inclusionary units from 84 units to 53 units.
